cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel multi-task learning architecture for computer vision tasks, specifically on the CityScapes dataset. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also incorporates recent advances in attention mechanisms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as soft-attention modules, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
